quran[20]{c,v,t,f}:
  15,71,"He said, “These are my daughters, if you must.”"
  15,72,"By your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>life, in their drunkenness they certainly do blunder!"
  15,73,"So the Shout took them away at sunrise."
  15,74,"And We turned it upside down and rained down upon them stones of hard clay."
  15,75,"Indeed, in that are certainly signs for those who contemplate."
  15,76,"And indeed, it{1}is certainly on an existing way.",footnotes:1:The ruins of the cities of the people of Lot.
  15,77,"Indeed, in that is certainly a sign for the believers."
  15,78,"And indeed, the fellows of the Thicket were certainly unjust,"
  15,79,"so We took retribution on them, and indeed, both are certainly in an evident archive."
  15,80,"And most surely, the fellows of Al-Hijr{1}disbelievedthe emissaries.",footnotes:1:Al-Hijrmeans the stone city which is located in northern Arabia and was inhabited by the people of Thamûd.
  15,81,"So We brought them Our signs, but they used to disregard them."
  15,82,"And of the mountains they used to carve homes, feeling safe."
  15,83,"But the Shout took them away by the morning,"
  15,84,"so all what they used to earn was of no avail to them."
  15,85,"And We did not create the heavens and the earth and whatever lies between them except with the truth{1}. And indeed, the Hour is coming, so pardon<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><i class=""s"">(with) </i>gracious pardoning.",footnotes:1:According to Ibn ʻAshour and other exegetes, ‘with the truth’ means ‘for a purpose’.
  15,86,"Indeed, your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord is the One Who is the All-Creating, the All-Knowing."
  15,87,"And most surely, We have brought you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>seven of the oft-repeated{1}and the great Recital{2}.",footnotes:1:The seven signs of the first surah.The Arabic word used is Qur’an which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  15,88,"Do<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not look longingly at the good things We have given some classes of them to enjoy, and do not grieve over them{1}, and lower your wing{2}towards the believers.",footnotes:1:The deniers.An expression that implies showing compassion.
  15,89,"And say, “Indeed, it is I—I who am the evident warner.”"
  15,90,"So too did We send down to those who divide among themselves—"
